The paper discusses a query language for annotated corpora, which is relevant to natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) tasks, falling under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions data manipulation and return value specification, which are common tasks in databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The language's expressive power and comparison with other query languages suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
